<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
================================================================================
  FS25_SlurryPipeSystem — Placeable Configuration Reference
  Oscar Mods
================================================================================
  This file is documentation only. It is not loaded by the mod.

  SPS supports TWO ways to add a placeable:

    1. INTERNAL  - Placeable config lives inside the SPS mod folder.
                   Used for the stock placeable kit shipped with SPS.
                   Path: configs/placeableConfigs/<name>/fillPoints.xml

    2. EMBEDDED  - Placeable config lives inside the modder's own placeable
                   XML as a <slurryPipeSystem> element under <placeable> root.
                   Used by third-party mods (and map-bundled placeables) to
                   ship SPS-ready placeables without touching the SPS mod.

  Both paths use IDENTICAL element schema. The only difference is location.
  Embedded configs win over internal manifest entries for the same placeable.
================================================================================
-->

<slurryPipeSystemPlaceableReference>


    <!-- ========================================================================
         INTERNAL CONFIG - FOLDER STRUCTURE & MANIFEST
    =========================================================================

    FS25_SlurryPipeSystem/
    └── configs/
        ├── spsConfigManifest.xml           ← lists every supported vehicle/placeable
        ├── couplerAnimations.xml           ← bundled coupler animations library
        │
        ├── data/                           ← stock placeables (mirrors data/ paths)
        │   └── placeables/
        │       └── <vendor>/<model>/
        │           ├── fillPoints.xml      ← placeable SPS config
        │           └── nodeTree.i3d        ← SPS nodes for this placeable
        │
        └── mods/                           ← third-party placeables (mirrors mods/)
            └── <FS25_ModFolderName>/...
                ├── fillPoints.xml
                └── nodeTree.i3d

    The bundled folder structure mirrors the runtime path of each placeable.
    Each placeable has a manifest entry of the form:

        <placeable path="data/placeables/rudolfHormann/cowBarnMedium/cowBarnMedium.xml"/>
        <placeable path="mods/FS25_Witcombe/map/placeables/cowBarn01/cowBarn01.xml"/>

    The "path" attribute must EXACTLY match the tail of the runtime placeable's
    configFileName (case-insensitive). When the match succeeds, SPS opens the
    bundled fillPoints.xml from a path computed by:

        1. Take the manifest path
        2. Strip the trailing XML filename
        3. Prepend "configs/"
        4. Append "fillPoints.xml"

    Example:
        path="data/placeables/rudolfHormann/cowBarnMedium/cowBarnMedium.xml"
          → configs/data/placeables/rudolfHormann/cowBarnMedium/fillPoints.xml

    ── OPTIONAL configFolder OVERRIDE ───────────────────────────────────────

    Many mods ship multiple placeable XMLs sharing the same parent folder
    (e.g. mods/UKBuildings/xml/cowShedUK.xml AND mods/UKBuildings/xml/
    cowShedUK_nonMilk.xml). Auto-derivation would point both entries at the
    same bundled fillPoints folder, which is impossible. Use the optional
    configFolder attribute to declare each entry's bundled location:

        <placeable path="mods/UKBuildings/xml/cowShedUK.xml"
                   configFolder="mods/UKBuildings/xml/cowShedUK"/>
        <placeable path="mods/UKBuildings/xml/cowShedUK_nonMilk.xml"
                   configFolder="mods/UKBuildings/xml/cowShedUK_nonMilk"/>

        → configs/mods/UKBuildings/xml/cowShedUK/fillPoints.xml
        → configs/mods/UKBuildings/xml/cowShedUK_nonMilk/fillPoints.xml

    Variant placeables that legitimately share the same i3d folder but need
    distinct SPS configs (e.g. data/placeables/rudolfHormann/cowBarnBig/
    cowBarnBig.xml, cowBarnBigGea.xml, cowBarnBigVector.xml) use the same
    pattern.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         BUNDLED VS EMBEDDED — WHEN TO USE WHICH
    =========================================================================

    INTERNAL/BUNDLED is for placeables SPS itself supports out of the box.
    The placeable XML stays untouched; the fillPoints.xml and nodeTree.i3d
    live inside the SPS mod folder. SPS knows about the placeable via a
    manifest entry.

    EMBEDDED is for third-party modders shipping SPS-ready placeables. The
    modder adds a <slurryPipeSystem> block directly inside their placeable
    XML. No SPS-side files needed. No manifest entry needed. The block
    self-contains everything: pipe couplings, coupler animations, fill plane
    bounds.

    Embedded ALWAYS wins over manifest. If both exist for the same
    configFileName, the embedded block is used.

    Map mods that ship placeables (e.g. shed buildings inside a custom map)
    can use either path. Embedded is preferred for self-containment.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         EMBEDDED CONFIG - INSIDE THE MODDER'S PLACEABLE XML
    =========================================================================

    A modder ships their placeable with a <slurryPipeSystem> element directly
    under <placeable> in the placeable's main XML. SPS detects this element
    at register time and uses the embedded block.

    Example modder XML:

        <placeable ...>
            ... vanilla placeable elements ...

            <slurryPipeSystem>
                <fillPlane node="fillPlaneNode" minY="0" maxY="2" fillType="LIQUIDMANURE"
                           shape="round" centreNodeName="planeCentre"
                           edgeNodeName="planeEdge"/>
                <pipeCouplings>
                    <pipeCoupling id="1" mountNodeName="myCoupler01" .../>
                </pipeCouplings>
                <couplerAnimations>
                    <couplerAnimation id="1" name="myClamp">
                        <part node="myClampHandle" .../>
                    </couplerAnimation>
                </couplerAnimations>
            </slurryPipeSystem>

            ... more vanilla placeable elements ...
        </placeable>

    For embedded configs, ALL nodes referenced by name are looked up inside
    the modder's own placeable i3d. No nodeTree.i3d file is loaded.

    Embedded ALWAYS wins over internal. Multiple modder versions of the same
    placeable type coexist independently — each instance reads its own XML.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         NODE TREE — i3d SETUP (INTERNAL CONFIG ONLY)
    =========================================================================

    For internal configs, all SPS nodes are authored in a separate nodeTree
    i3d file placed alongside fillPoints.xml. The nodeTree is loaded via
    loadI3DFile at register time. The nodeTree root must contain a single
    container child whose name matches an existing node in the placeable's
    own component hierarchy. The manager parents the nodeTree contents into
    that node.

    Do NOT use cloneSharedI3DNode — cloning breaks skin bindings.

    For EMBEDDED configs there is no nodeTree concept — all node names
    resolve against the modder's own placeable i3d directly.

    ── NODE TREE STRUCTURE (internal configs) ────────────────────────────────

    nodeTree root (TransformGroup)
    └── <containerName> (TransformGroup)         ← matches a placeable i3d node
        ├── pipeCouplers (TransformGroup)
        │   ├── SPS_pipeCoupler01                ← coupling 1 mount point
        │   │   └── SPS_pipeCoupler01Arcs
        │   │       ├── SPS_pipeCoupler01Arc01   ← arc detection node left
        │   │       └── SPS_pipeCoupler01Arc02   ← arc detection node right
        │   └── (repeat for SPS_pipeCoupler02 etc. if required)
        │
        ├── fillPlaneNodes (TransformGroup)      ← detection nodes for fill plane
        │   ├── slurryPlaneCentre                ← centre of fill area (all shapes)
        │   ├── slurryPlaneEdge                  ← edge — round shape only
        │   ├── slurryPlaneCorner1               ← first corner — rectangle only
        │   └── slurryPlaneCorner2               ← opposite corner — rectangle only
        │
        └── effects (TransformGroup)             ← optional inlet effect nodes
            └── effect (TransformGroup)          ← PipeEffect shape node
                └── pipeEffectSmoke              ← smoke/particle emitter

    ── NODE PLACEMENT RULES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

    SPS_pipeCouplerXX
        Place at the physical centre of the coupling mouth on the building.
        Rotation: local Z-axis pointing outward away from the building wall.

    SPS_pipeCouplerXXArcs (group node) and Arc01 / Arc02
        Place symmetrically either side of the coupler mouth:
            1.5m left and right in local X, 2.5m forward in local Z.
        These define the arc detection triangle. A connecting vehicle or chain
        terminus must have overlapping arc nodes for a connection to be offered.

    slurryPlaneCentre
        Place at ground level at the centre of the slurry pit or tank opening.
        Used as the XZ sampling position for surface height detection.

    slurryPlaneEdge (round shape only)
        Place at the edge of the circular pit at ground level.
        Distance from centre to edge defines the detection radius.

    slurryPlaneCorner1 / slurryPlaneCorner2 (rectangle shape only)
        Place at two diagonally opposite corners of the rectangular pit at
        ground level. Defines the detection rectangle.

    effect / pipeEffectSmoke
        Place at the physical inlet point where slurry enters the store
        (e.g. top of the inlet pipe). The PipeEffect streams visually from
        the connecting pipe end to this node. pipeEffectSmoke is repositioned
        dynamically as stream length changes.

    ── DEPLOYABLE COUPLING ANIM NODE ─────────────────────────────────────────

    When a coupling has deployable="true", the optional <pipeAnimNode>
    element specifies a node in the placeable's own i3d (not the nodeTree)
    to rotate when the coupling is deployed. This is used to swing open
    a gate, lid or cover that conceals the coupling when not in use.

    The node is driven directly by SPS — it is not controlled by vanilla
    animation. rx, ry, rz are the Euler rotation in degrees applied when
    deployed. When undeployed the rotation is not modified.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         FILL PLANE SURFACE DETECTION
    =========================================================================

    The fill plane determines two things:
        1. Whether a fill arm upper node is inside the store's fill area.
        2. The current slurry surface Y position used to check whether the
           arm lower node is submerged for flow to begin.

    Surface Y is read from the engine-managed fill plane node each tick. The
    fill plane node Y is driven by the engine based on current fill level,
    moving between minY (empty) and maxY (full) in the node's local space.
    SPS converts this to world Y via getWorldTranslation on the node.

    shape="round"
        Uses centreNode and edgeNode to define a circular detection zone.
        Radius = distance between centreNode and edgeNode at placement time.

    shape="rectangle"
        Uses centreNode, corner1Node and corner2Node to define a rectangle.

    If shape is omitted, no shape-based detection is used and connection is
    confirmed by the fill arm's own trigger volume check only.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         <slurryPipeSystem> ROOT ELEMENT
    =========================================================================

    All SPS configuration for a placeable lives inside a single
    <slurryPipeSystem> element. For internal configs this is the root of
    fillPoints.xml. For embedded configs this is a child of <placeable>.

    <slurryPipeSystem agitator="bool">
        <nodeTree filename="nodeTree.i3d"/>            (internal only)
        <fillPlane .../>
        <hideNodes>...</hideNodes>
        <hideCollisions>...</hideCollisions>
        <pipeCouplings>...</pipeCouplings>
        <pipeAnimNode .../>
        <couplerAnimations>...</couplerAnimations>     (optional)
    </slurryPipeSystem>

    ATTRIBUTES on <slurryPipeSystem>:

    agitator        true = a SPS-controlled agitator can be inserted into
                    this placeable's fill plane to enable agitation effects.
                    Default: false.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         <nodeTree>
    =========================================================================

    <nodeTree filename="nodeTree.i3d"/>

    filename    Path to the nodeTree i3d relative to this fillPoints.xml.
                Internal configs only. Omit entirely for embedded configs
                (the modder's placeable i3d is used directly).

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         <fillPlane>
    =========================================================================

    <fillPlane
        node="..."
        minY="N.N"
        maxY="N.N"
        fillType="..."
        shape="round|rectangle"
        centreNodeName="..."
        edgeNodeName="..."
        corner1NodeName="..."
        corner2NodeName="..."
    />

    node            Engine-animated fill plane node name in the placeable i3d.
                    The engine moves this node's Y between minY and maxY as
                    the storage fills and empties.
    minY            Local Y of the fill plane node when the storage is empty.
    maxY            Local Y of the fill plane node when the storage is full.
    fillType        Fill type string for this storage. Default: LIQUIDMANURE.

    shape="round"       Circular arm detection zone.
                        Requires: centreNodeName, edgeNodeName.
    shape="rectangle"   Rectangular arm detection zone.
                        Requires: centreNodeName, corner1NodeName, corner2NodeName.

    centreNodeName  Node at the centre of the fill area.
    edgeNodeName    Node at the edge — round shape only.
    corner1NodeName First corner of the rectangle — rectangle shape only.
    corner2NodeName Diagonally opposite corner — rectangle shape only.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         <hideNodes>
    =========================================================================

    <hideNodes>
        <node name="..."/>
        <node name="..."/>
    </hideNodes>

    Lists nodes in the placeable i3d to hide visually when SPS is active.
    Used to suppress vanilla drive-in trigger meshes, fill towers, ramps or
    any geometry that conflicts with SPS pipe connections.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         <hideCollisions>
    =========================================================================

    <hideCollisions>
        <node name="..."/>
        <node name="..."/>
    </hideCollisions>

    Lists collision nodes in the placeable i3d to disable when SPS is active.
    Used to remove vanilla drive-in ramp collisions or fill tower collision
    bodies that would block vehicle access or interfere with pipe placement.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         <pipeAnimNode>
    =========================================================================

    <pipeAnimNode node="..." rx="N" ry="N" rz="N"/>

    node        Node name in the placeable's own i3d (NOT the nodeTree).
                Rotated when a deployable coupling on this placeable is
                deployed by the player.
    rx ry rz    Euler rotation in DEGREES applied to the node when deployed.
                When undeployed, SPS does not touch the node rotation —
                vanilla animation or the default state controls it.

    Omit this element if the placeable has no deployable couplings or no
    visual rotation is needed when a coupling is deployed.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         <pipeCouplings>
    =========================================================================

    <pipeCouplings>
        <pipeCoupling
            id="N"
            mountNodeName="..."
            flowDirection="DISCHARGE|FILL|BOTH"
            valveType="MANUAL|HYDRAULIC|NONE"
            deployable="bool"
            connector="male|female"
            connectorAnimation="N"
            valveAnimation="N"
        >
            <effects inletDistance="N.N">
                <effectNode effectNode="..."/>
                <effectNode effectNode="..."/>
            </effects>
        </pipeCoupling>
    </pipeCouplings>

    id              Unique integer ID for this coupling within the placeable.

    mountNodeName   Node name of the coupling mount point.
                    Internal: a node in the nodeTree.
                    Embedded: a node in the modder's placeable i3d.
                    Arc detection nodes must exist as children:
                        <mountNodeName>Arcs
                            <mountNodeName>Arc01
                            <mountNodeName>Arc02

    flowDirection
        DISCHARGE   Only allows slurry to be pumped INTO this store.
                    Vehicles cannot pull slurry out via this coupling.
        FILL        Only allows slurry to be pulled OUT of this store.
        BOTH        No restriction — flow in either direction is permitted.

    valveType
        MANUAL      Valve is opened by the player at the coupling using long
                    press R. Standard for placeable couplings that have a
                    physical valve handle.
        HYDRAULIC   Valve is cab-controlled via SPS_TOGGLE_FLOW. No manual
                    interaction at the coupling.
        NONE        No valve — flow begins immediately when connected and
                    pump is on. Standard for placeable store couplings whose
                    physical inlet has no valve.

    deployable      true = coupling is hidden by default and deployed by the
                    player via long press R when within range. Used for ports
                    concealed on a building wall when not in use. Pair with
                    <pipeAnimNode> to rotate a cover or gate on deploy.

    connector       "male" or "female". Controls which end of the connecting
                    bez pipe is shown at this coupling. Default: "female".

    connectorAnimation  Optional animation id from <couplerAnimations>.
                        Plays forward on connect, reverse on disconnect.
                        Used for clamp / collar visuals.

    valveAnimation      Optional animation id from <couplerAnimations>.
                        Plays forward on valve open, reverse on close.
                        Used for valve handle rotations.

    <effects> (optional child of <pipeCoupling>)
        Declares the visual inlet stream shown when slurry flows into the
        store via this coupling.

        inletDistance   Stream length in metres from the pipe end to the
                        physical inlet point inside the store. Default: 1.5.

        <effectNode effectNode="..."/>     (first child)
            effectNode = node name in the nodeTree (internal) or placeable
            i3d (embedded) for the PipeEffect shape. The shape's first child
            is automatically used as the visible pipe mesh.

        <effectNode effectNode="..."/>     (second child)
            effectNode = node name of the smoke / particle emitter that
            sits at the inlet end of the stream. The manager repositions
            this node as the stream length changes.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         <couplerAnimations>
    =========================================================================

    <couplerAnimations>
        <couplerAnimation id="N" name="...">
            <part
                node="..."
                startTime="N.N"
                endTime="N.N"
                startRot="X Y Z"
                endRot="X Y Z"
                startTrans="X Y Z"
                endTrans="X Y Z"
            />
            <part .../>
            ...
        </couplerAnimation>
    </couplerAnimations>

    Each <couplerAnimation> is referenced from <pipeCoupling> by id (via
    connectorAnimation="N" or valveAnimation="N"). Animations are scoped
    to the placeable that declares them — there is no global namespace.

    For internal configs the bundled file configs/couplerAnimations.xml
    is used. For embedded configs, the modder declares animations inline
    inside their <slurryPipeSystem> block.

    couplerAnimation
        id          Unique integer id within this <couplerAnimations> block.
                    Referenced by <pipeCoupling connectorAnimation="N"/> and
                    <pipeCoupling valveAnimation="N"/>.
        name        Human-readable name (logged at load, otherwise unused).

    part            One animated node within this animation. Multiple parts
                    can be combined into a single animation (e.g. two clamp
                    handles closing together).

        node        Node name. Must exist as a descendant of the coupling's
                    mountNode subtree at registration time. Resolved via
                    depth-first search from the mountNode.

        startTime   Animation time in seconds when this part starts moving.
        endTime     Animation time in seconds when this part stops moving.
                    Animation duration is the maximum endTime across all parts.

        startRot    Rotation in DEGREES at startTime. "X Y Z" Euler.
        endRot      Rotation in DEGREES at endTime. Linear interpolation
                    between startRot and endRot during the part's active range.

        startTrans  Translation in METRES at startTime. "X Y Z".
        endTrans    Translation in METRES at endTime.

    Both rotation and translation are optional — declare whichever the part
    needs. Forward play (connect / valve open) animates from start to end.
    Reverse play (disconnect / valve close) animates from end to start.

    ======================================================================== -->

</slurryPipeSystemPlaceableReference>